{% layout 'default' %}

<section class="login">
	<aside class="login__guide login-guide">
		<h1 class="login-guide__title">Let's get started!</h1>
		<p>
			To begin using this Micropub client, please login with your domain. Once we know it's you, we can start publishing to your Micropub server.
		</p>

		<h2>Not sure if you're up to speed?</h2>

		<p>A Micropub client works in tandem with a Micropub server. If you've not had a chance to <a href="https://github.com/hirusi/Celestial/blob/master/README.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">look at Celestial's readme</a> yet, it would be a good idea to do so now. In general, we are just an interface. The actual publishing task (writing files or data to your website) is a job assigned to a Micropub server. This is by design. <a href="https://indieweb.org/Micropub/Servers" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">You can pick from plenty</a>.

		<p>If you're rocking a static site like I am, I highly recommend <a href="https://github.com/getindiekit/indiekit" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Indiekit by Paul Robert Lloyd</a>.</p>

		<p>Additionally, when you login with your domain, we expect to read a few things from your website's discovery page (generally, your home page). As an example, we could be looking for the following HTML tags in your <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> tag:</p>

		<pre><code>&lt;link href="https://indieauth.com/auth" rel="authorization_endpoint"&gt;
&lt;link href="https://tokens.indieauth.com/token" rel="token_endpoint"&gt;
&lt;link href="http://micropub.yourdomain.com/micropub" rel="micropub"&gt;</code></pre>

		<p>If you're a technical user, you may also specify this data in your website's HTTP headers. Since you're a technical user, I expect you will be able to find your way around on this, based on whatever tools you are using to host your site. ðŸ™‚</p>
	</aside>

	<main class="login__main">
		<form
			action="/login/try/"
			method="post"
			enctype="application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
			class="form form--login login-form"
		>
			<fieldset>
				<legend>Login</legend>
				<div class="field-group">
					<label for="url">Web Address:</label>
					<p
						class="field-group__description"
						id="field-group__description--url"
					>If the web address you enter redirects elsewhere, we will follow the redirect up to one redirect before calling off our search.</p>
					<input
						id="url"
						name="me"
						placeholder="https://yourdomain.com"
						class="login-form__web-address"
						type="url"
						autocomplete="on"
						autofocus
						aria-describedby="field-group__description--url"
					/>
				</div>
			</fieldset>

			<button type="submit" class="login-form__submit">Sign In</button>

			<input name="_csrf" type="hidden" value="{{ csrfToken }}" />

			<input type="hidden" name="timezone" class="login-form__timezone" value="" />
			
		</form>
	</main>
</section>